    {
        "content": "<blockquote>\n<p>the answer is that <code>Vector</code> is a subtype</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Is it a subtype? It doesn't look like one:<br>\n<a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/v4.19.0/src/Init/Data/Vector/Basic.lean#L25-L27\">https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/v4.19.0/src/Init/Data/Vector/Basic.lean#L25-L27</a></p>",
        "id": 521468377,
        "sender_full_name": "Francisco Giordano",
        "timestamp": 1748718507
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Right, I guess it was a subtype in the general sense, not in the literal sense of <code>Subtype</code>, and in any case they look exactly the same</p>",
        "id": 521469272,
